  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1+H4 CSM at 100 with Risk-Off High regime driven by US inflation fears pushing US10Y to 4.595 and VIX spiking 6.78%, while copper -4.81% and silver -9.13% confirm commodity demand destruction. USDCHF is the cleanest expression with D1+H4 strong buy and H4 1212 at 78, while GBPUSD carries the highest short conviction as GBP sits last on both D1 and H4 CSM with GBPJPY correlation at 0.94 amplifying any GBP flush. AUD shows a critical 39-point H4/D1 CSM divergence with H4 fading to 26 versus D1 at 65, making AUDUSD longs a trap and AUDJPY D1 buy signals unreliable intraday.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: USDCAD CMP 60 with D1 59 rising and H4 70 accelerating, clean USD bid into CAD weakness\nFading: GBPUSD CMP 36 H4 13 collapsing, NZDUSD CMP 43 H4 17 collapsing, EURUSD CMP 37 H4 13 dropping\n\nWATCH\nWTI at 105.4 up 4.2 percent on energy supply disruption \u2014 USDCAD faces conflicting pressure, a CAD bounce breaks the H4 uptrend\nUS 2Y yield breaking from flatness triggers USDJPY extension through H4 buy signal toward prior highs\nSilver extending below 77 confirms industrial demand collapse \u2014 AUDUSD accelerates lower through H4 sell target",
